# Built SPA — generated by `npm run build` (vite outDir), NOT committed.
# It is content-hash-named build output, so committing it churns the worktree
# on every rebuild. Instead it is regenerated from frontend/ source at the two
# moments that need it and force-included into the wheel via pyproject's
# `[tool.poetry] include` (so end users still `pip install` a prebuilt SPA with
# no node toolchain):
#   - wheel creation — the `publish-dashboard` CI job builds it before `poetry build`
#   - dev/source installs — `task install` / `task install:from-source` / e2e all
#     run `npm run build` first
# The runtime no-ops the SPA mount when static/ is absent (app.py `_mount_spa`),
# so a source checkout without a build still serves the API fine.
brainpalace_dashboard/static/
